      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Roughly break the chocolate sandwich biscuit biscuits into a food processor. Blitz the biscuits on a high speed until they resemble fine breadcrumbs. Melt the butter in a saucepan then add the biscuit crumbs and mix until it’s thoroughly combined.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Divide the biscuits between 9 muffin cases and press down with the back of a teaspoon to form a base, refrigerate for 1 hour.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "To make the filling add the cream cheese, Irish cream liqueur, icing sugar, chocolate in a large bowl and lightly whip together. Fold in the whipped cream until thoroughly combined.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Divide the mixture into the muffin cases and refrigerate for at least 2-3 hours.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "To serve simply remove from the muffin cases and sprinkle over a little extra grated chocolate.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Test with a skewer. It should come out with a few moist crumbs, not wet batter. Don't open the oven before three-quarters of the bake time.",
              "cause": "Underbaked, or the oven door opened too early.",
              "symptom": "Cake sinks in the middle"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Check at the minimum bake time and every five minutes after. Weigh flour for cake recipes, cup measures vary by 20% depending on how you scoop.",
              "cause": "Overbaked, or too much flour measured by cup not weight.",
              "symptom": "Cake is dry"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Drop the temperature by 10°C and check earlier. Domed cakes can be trimmed flat once cool.",
              "cause": "Oven too hot, or batter too thick.",
              "symptom": "Top cracked or domed"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Check baking powder is fresh. It loses lift after six months. Use room-temperature butter and eggs so the batter holds air.",
              "cause": "Raising agent stale or omitted, or butter and eggs cold.",
              "symptom": "Cake didn't rise"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Variations",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Citrus version: replace the vanilla with the zest of an orange or lemon.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Nut-free: swap ground almonds for desiccated coconut or extra plain flour, weight for weight.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Best fresh. Leftovers keep two days in the fridge; reheat covered with a splash of liquid.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A British home cook's dish. It sits among the recipes families remember without thinking about, the kind that gets adjusted across generations and never quite the same twice.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
